				<text>37.1.5.3 Factory machines 2</text>
		</name>
    <questiontext format="moodle_auto_format">
				<text><![CDATA[<p class="HELM_exercise">Exercise</p>
A factory has \({@ma@}\) machines. \({@em@}\) of these have been given an experimental modification. In the first week after this modification, problems are reported with \({@de@}\) of the machines. What is the probability that excatly \(2\) of the modified machines are among the \({@de@}\) with problems assuming that all machines are equally likely to give problems?<p><b>Write your answer as a rational number (fraction).</b></p>
<p>[[input:ans1]] [[validation:ans1]]&nbsp;[[feedback:prt1]]</p>]]></text>
		</questiontext>
    <generalfeedback format="moodle_auto_format">
				<text><![CDATA[<h4 class="HELM_solution">Solution</h4>
<p>There are \(\binom{{@ma@}}{{@de@}}\) possible different selections of \({@de@}\) machines and all are equally likely, \(\binom{{@em@}}{2}\) different choices of two modified machines, and \(\binom{{@nm@}}{{@de2@}}\) different choices of \({@de2@}\) non-modified machines. Hence the required probability is \[
\dfrac{\binom{{@em@}}{2}\times\binom{{@nm@}}{{@de2@}}}{\binom{{@ma@}}{{@de@}}} = {@ta1@}
\]
</p>]]></text>
		</generalfeedback>
